			<div class="commentcount">224</div>

				<p>The best trick to get the ganache to cling but not run too much 
is to chill the frosted cake before you use it. Cold is your best friend
 when assembling cakes. Because the peanut butter icing will be cold, it
 will dribble down more slowly. Just only pour a tablespoon or two at a 
time–you can always add more if it doesn’t drip down enough.</p>
	</li>

		

	
