			<div class="commentcount">1168</div>

				<p>Well, I finally slayed the beast. Made the cakes in two layers, 
froze them overnight and also made and chilled the frosting overnight 
too. Thawed cakes next morning, slathered in frosting (no crumb coat, so
 it as a bit messy) and then made ganache. Tasted as good as I had 
always hoped it would. So thrilled I finally did it! This was my first 
SK cook!</p>
	</li>

		

	
