			<div class="commentcount">1169</div>

				<p>I made this cake for my brother’s birthday, and the entire family
 loved it. The cake itself was super moist–so good! I added a bit more 
peanut butter to the frosting (I love the stuff), but I had to forget 
about the ganache. As much as I’m sure it’s even better with that extra 
chocolate, this cake is definitely still great without. </p>
<p>Also, I have some family members who don’t like peanut butter, and 
they still had seconds of this cake. I think that if you like peanut 
butter, you can taste it, but it’s subtle enough that most people will 
enjoy it.</p>
<p>A real winner!</p>
	</li>

		

	
